h1. Acceptance Criteria

*As a* an Author

*I want to* use a design system custom presentation component

*So that* I am working within the framework of the NOVA design system

1.The custom presentation component's authoring dialogue must feature the following tabs:
 # 
 ## Overview
 ## Styles
 ## Analytics
 ## Advanced
 # All specifications outlined in the "NOVA ISA Authoring PlatformV2.0.xlsx" requirements document must be met.
 # Click stream tags should initially use the authored values specified in the template. However:
 ## These values can be overridden by the ones defined directly within the component.

 * *General*
 ** Define V2 Component
 ** Add to new clientlib
 ** Define new style consuming the listed tokens
 ** htl changes listed below:

 
h1. Technical Details

Reference structure for new DS components styles:

 
{code:java}
.cmp-button {
    // Enterprise OTB variables defined for base unbranded styling
    // ex. --background: #CCCCCC
}
.cmp-button {
    // component styles go here consuming token variables
    // ex. background: var(--background);
    
    .nested-prop {
        // ex. border-top: var(--border-top)
    }
} {code}
 

Brand Clientlibs Structure:
{code:java}
// Auto Generated from Design System
.cmp-component.theme {
    // Generated Brand Design System token variables
    // ex. --background: #7F175C;
}{code}

Safety Bar:

-{color:#172b4d}1.The text in the safety bar is displaying only 2 to 3 words in a row, and the text does not fully occupy the available space.(refer issue 1 screen shot){color}-  {color:#57d9a3}Issues fixed and retested on 01/23{color}

-{color:#de350b}2.When "ISI Expansion Direction" is set to "Upwards," the following issues occur:{color}-

-{color:#de350b}-The collapse buttons are not displayed.{color}-
-{color:#de350b}-After expanding first safety bar ,The text is not showing in the second safety bar and vice versa.(refer issue 2 screen shot){color}- {color:#de350b}Issues fixed and retested on 01/31{color}

{-}-3.When the "Override System Default Value" checkbox is checked in the Analytics tab, only the free text field should be displayed, and all other fields should be hidden. However, all fields are currently visible{-}.- {color:#de350b}Issues fixed and retested on 01/31{color}

-4.Custom class values are not being passed or reflected in the inspect element.- *- Issue Fixed & retested on 01/22*

-{color:#de350b}5.Style properties are shown in the component when authored for the first time, but after making any adjustments, the style values are no longer visible in the component.(Refer below test URL){color}-  {color:#de350b}Issues fixed and retested on 01/31{color}

{-}-6.Collapsed ISI Text, Expanded ISI Text, Bottom ISI Text, and Indication ISI Text are not displaying fully{-}.- {color:#de350b}Issues fixed and retested on 01/31{color}

TEST URL : [https://admp-test-auth.abbvie.com/editor.html/content/nova/Test/safety-bar.html]

   

-Additional Issues :-

{}7. Experience fragment include, pulls ivy clientlibs redirecting & failing page due to missing AbbviePageInfo\{-} -- *Issue Fixed and retested on 01/29*

-[-https://admp-test-auth.abbvie.com/sites.html/content/nova/Test/mukesh-]-

{}{}8. Brand Field displayed under Multifield needs to be removed. ---{-}{{-}}{color:#00875a} *Issue Fixed and retested on 01/29*{color}

 

{color:#172b4d}*Retest Issues (01/31):*{color}

{color:#172b4d}1.When the "Override System Default Value" checkbox is enabled and a clickstream tag is manually entered, the manually entered clickstream tag does not appear in the console when expanding or collapsing the Safety Bar. This was working before .{color}

{color:#172b4d}2. When the "Override System Default Value" checkbox is disabled, the tab name displays as "undefined." It should be replaced with "XXX" since the tab name applies to tab headers.{color}

{color:#172b4d}Refer attached 'Safety bar retest' doc for reference (issue #3) {color}

{color:#172b4d}[https://admp-test-auth.abbvie.com/editor.html/content/nova/Test/safety-bar-retest.html]{color}

 

 

!image-2025-01-24-12-56-41-051.png!

URL : [https://admp-test-auth.abbvie.com/editor.html/content/nova/Test/image/formulary-data.html]

Formulary component  (V2 template) Issues and observation . Please check and advise.
 
1.{-}Tool tip not appearing for most of the fields.{-} -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
2. -When the "Override System Default Value" checkbox is checked in the Analytics tab, only the free text field should be displayed,
and all other fields should be hidden. However, all fields are currently visible.- -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
3.{-}When the second formulary is added, the Subtitle and Bottom text fields are disabled.{-}- -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
4.{-}The Email and Print buttons are displayed on the left; they should be on the right side.{-} - -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
5.The link type dropdown should be disabled for the Email and Print child buttons, but all link types are still selectable. - *As per the below comments, this is an expected behavior.*
6 -None of the style properties are functioning or reflecting on the formulary component after authoring.- -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
7.{-}Border Color is not selectable{-} -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
8.For the Print button, the default title 'Email Plans' appears, while for the Email button, the title 'Button Text' appears. The titles are inconsistent. - *As per the below comments, this is an expected behavior.*
9.{-}Clicking the Print button should direct to the Salesforce page, but it doesn't. Additionally, clicking the 'Email Plans' button throws an error: 'Window.external.notify is not a function.'{-}
-Is this expected behavior in the AEM editor? since this functionality is primarily testable on an iPad.-
10. -In the Change Location button, the 'Choose State' and 'Retrieving Counties' dropdowns are not showing up.- -{color:#00875a} Issue fixed and Retested on 31/Jan/25{color}
11. The zip code field is allowing more than 5 digits without showing an error. -{*}Please refer Issue-14{*}
12. The "Subtitle" and "Bottom Text" text fields are in grey color, not white. -{color:#de350b} Issue Exists{color}

*Additional Defects*

-13. Email & Print buttons - themes not showing (Related to Nested container)- 

*Retesting Issues on 31/Jan/25*
14. Zip code text field is currently displayed as a standard text field with increment and decrement icons. Also, Tooltip description for the zipcode field is not suitable.
15. In the styles tab, all text fields, along with the increment and decrement icons, now have a default value set to 0. 
Previously, up and down arrow symbols were displayed instead of the increment and decrement icons, with no value. - *Is this expected?*

