h2. Out of the box animations should include:
 * Fade In
 * Fade In Down
 * Fade In Left
 * Fade In Up
 * Fade In Right
 * Pulse
 * Grow In

h2. Included Components
 * Button

h2. Technical Details:
 * Animation Authoring Tab
 ** Animation style (select - default none)
 ** Animation duration (numfield - seconds)
 ** Animation delay (numfield - seconds)
 ** Animate once (checkbox - default checked)

CSS Driven animations triggered by JS event
 * Elements will be tagged with
 ** data-animate-type = \{animation-style}
 ** data-animate-once = \{"true/false"}
 ** inline style attribute = \{animation-duration:${animation-duration};animation-delay:${animation-delay}}
 ** data-animated = \{"false"}

When a slide loads, tab opens or modal opens elements come in view should update data-animated to "true"

If a tab is switched away from, or modal closes:
 * if data-animate-once = false, do not update data-animated to false
 * else data-animated should be switched back to false

*Animations should be written as:*
{code:java}
[data-animate-animated="animation-style"][data-animated="true"]{
  -webkit-animation-name: animation-style;
  animation-name: animation-style;
}
@keyframes animation-style {
  from {

  }
  to {

  }
}{code}
_Example:_
{code:java}
[data-animate-animated="novaFadeInDown"][data-animated="true"] {
  -webkit-animation-name: novaFadeInDown;
  animation-name: novaFadeInDown;
}
@-webkit-keyframes novaFadeInDown {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    -webkit-transform: translate3d(0, -100%, 0);
    transform: translate3d(0, -100%, 0);
  }  to {
    opacity: 1;
    -webkit-transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0);
    transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0);
  }
} {code}

* Consistently update labels for link and modal to Link to Slide  and Overlay (update should happen on IVA Button,  Image, Callout).
 * When link Type is selected as “Link to Slide”  Show the path field, Overlay ID text field and show a new dropdown field for “Deep linking” into Carousel and Tab;
 ** Drop down will include (None Tab, Carousel options).
 * When tab or Carousel is selected;
 ** Show the respective fields for Carousel ID/TabId and Carousel Index/Tab index.

Developer is expected to use the dialog include option for the fields, link type, overlay ID, Tab Id, Tab Index, Carousel ID, Carousel Index, so they are consistenly used on all three components.

